<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="30" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tree</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-23"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 23, 1888</date>.
                            (Received December 3.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 417.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy of
                        a letter addressed to me by the minister of foreign affairs, giving me
                        formal notice of the surrender of the man Sambolino into the hands of Mr.
                        Heidelberg on board the steamer <hi rend="italic">Westernland</hi> on the
                        10th instant.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lambert Tree.</hi></signed></closer>
                    <frus:attachment>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No.
                            417.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Prince <persName type="from">de
                                    Chimay</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Tree</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-19"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 19,
                                    1888</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Minister</hi>: Referring to your letter of the
                            6th of this month, I have the honor to inform your excellency that the
                            man Sambolino, Adolph, was conducted on board of the steamer <hi rend="italic">Westernland</hi>, Saturday, the 10th of November, and
                            surrendered into the hands of Mr. Heidelberg.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Prince de
                            Chimay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </frus:attachment>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>